<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 12:53PM EST  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED RISK OF WILDFIRE SPREAD THIS AFTERNOON ACROSS PORTIONS
OF EASTERN OHIO...
Here is a fire danger statement issued in coordination with the
Ohio Division of Forestry.
A combination of dry and breezy conditions will create an
elevated risk of fire spread this afternoon into early this
evening. Minimum relative humidity values are forecast to drop to
between 25 and 30 percent. Sustained wind of 10 to 15 MPH with
gusts up to 30 MPH are expected.
Residents are urged to exercise caution if handling any potential
ignition sources, such as machinery, cigarettes, or matches. If
dry grasses and tree litter begin to burn, the fire will have the
potential to spread rapidly.
Ohio law prohibits burning in the spring from 6AM to 6PM...March
1st through May 31st.</description>
